---
layout: layout.njk
title: KenKen 4x4 Puzzle
navtitle: KenKen 4x4
pageCss: "/assets/css/kenken4.css"
---
<div class="d-flex flex-column align-items-center">
  <div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-2 mb-3">
    <div id="stopwatch"><i class="fa-solid fa-stopwatch"></i><span id="timer"> 0:00</span></div>
    <button class="btn btn-success" id='checkPuzzle' onclick="showCheckModal()">Check Puzzle</button>
  </div>
  <div id="kenken"></div>
  <div class="mb-3" id="tiles">
    <button class="tile" data-number="1">1</button>
    <button class="tile" data-number="2">2</button>
    <button class="tile" data-number="3">3</button>
    <button class="tile" data-number="4">4</button>
    <button class="tile eraser" data-number=""><i class="fa-solid fa-eraser"></i></button>
  </div>
  <div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-2 mb-3">
    <div style="gap: 10px;">
      <i class="fa-solid fa-paintbrush fa-xl"></i>
      <label class="custom-switch">
        <input type="checkbox" id="pencilModeSwitch">
        <span class="slider"></span>
      </label>
      <i class="fa-solid fa-pencil fa-xl" style="color:gray"></i>
    </div>
    <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary" id="undo-button"><i class="fa-solid fa-rotate-left"></i></button>
    <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary" id="redo-button"><i class="fa-solid fa-rotate-right"></i></button>
    <button id="pauseButton" class="btn btn-outline-secondary"><i class="fa-solid fa-pause"></i></button>
    <button class="btn btn-danger" id="clear-game">Reset</button>
  </div>
  <hr>
  <p class="text-center text-muted" id="daily-number"></p>
  <div class="text-center">
    <a href="mailto:raj@mathplusacademy.com?subject=Bug Report for Daily 24 Game" class="btn btn-outline-danger">
      Report a Bug
    </a>
  </div>
  {% Modal 
    id="help",
    title="How to Play", 
    body="
      <ol>
        <li>Fill in each cell with a number from 1 to 4
        <li>Every row and column contains each number exactly once
        <li>The cells in a colored region combine to make the target value using given operation (+, -, x, or รท)
        <br>Note: Numbers is a colored region may occur more than once as long as they don't violate rule #2
      </ol>
      Use the number tiles below the puzzle or keyboard to enter numbers into the grid. You may use pencil mode (<i class='fa-solid fa-pencil' style='color:gray'></i>) to mark potential numbers in a cell<br>
      Use the Check Puzzle button to verify your solution. If you get stuck, you can reset the puzzle using the Reset Puzzle button.<br>
      <img src='/assets/images/kenken4play.gif' class='img-fluid w-50 d-block mx-auto' alt='Sample KenKen Game'>"
  %}
  {% Modal 
    id="checkPuzzle",
    title="Check Puzzle" 
  %}
  {% Modal 
    id="welcome",
    title="Welcome!", 
    body="
      <ol>
        <li>Fill in each cell with a number from 1 to 4
        <li>Every row and column contains each number exactly once
        <li>The cells in a colored region combine to make the target value using given operation (+, -, x, or รท)
        <br>Note: Numbers is a colored region may occur more than once as long as they don't violate rule #2
      </ol>
      <img src='/assets/images/kenken4play.gif' class='img-fluid w-50 d-block mx-auto' alt='Sample KenKen Game'>
      <div class='text-center'><button id='startButton' class='btn btn-success'>Start</button></div>
      "
  %}
  {% Modal 
    id="pause",
    title="Game Paused", 
    body="
      The game is paused.
      <div class='text-center'><button id='resumeButton' class='btn btn-outline-primary'>Resume</button></div>
      "
  %}

</div>
<script src="/assets/js/kenken4.js"></script>
